{
  "texts": [
    "We then demonstrate that training an AI algorithm on this slightly biased dataset results in the algorithm not only adopting the bias but further amplifying it.",
    "Next, we show that when humans interact with the biased AI, their initial bias increases (Fig. 1a; human-AI interaction).",
    "This bias amplification does not occur in an interaction including only human participants (Fig. 1b; human-human interaction).",
    "Fig. 1 | Human-AI interaction creates a feedback loop that makes humans more biased (experiment 1).",
    "a, Human-AI interaction."
  ]
}